body.p: A visualization of English language science fiction, fantasy or horror novels, in terms of whether they are in a series or standalone.

ul.li: Book data courtesy of the database dumps that ISFDB make available each week. Also please be aware of this chart on the ISFDB site which charts similar statistics.

body.p: This report/site has no affiliation with ISFDB or Wikipedia other than (a) using their data as described above, and (b) me being an end-user of/ data contributor to their sites (see here and here). I am not affiliated with any magazine, publisher, author, etc either.

ul.li: Non English-language novels are excluded from the stats to avoid any risk of super-popular and widely translated franchises such as Lord of the Rings or Harry Potter distorting the stats. (A better solution to only use works in their original language should be feasible, but hasn't yet been implemented.)

For similar reasons of simplicity, short stories, anthologies, collections, etc are omitted, as they are likely to distort the stats. (e.g. if a short story such as The Cold Equations or The Ones Who Walk Away from Omelas gets many reprints over the years, how would that best be counted?)
More stuff like this on my website or my Twitter feed.
